PROPOSAL {#proposal .unnumbered}
========

::: {style="color: my-grey"}

------------------------------------------------------------------------
:::

The Open Library's commitment to providing resources to as wide a
population as possible makes it an invaluable service for all.
Introducting new selection features, improving user experience on mobile
devices, and making available authoritative book pages is an important
part of continuing the Opern Library's mission.

My proposed contributions would include:

- **Provide filtering funcitonality to existing
  books** --- By adding a bridge between the
  user-facing web components and the underlying database, users will
  be able to select from a list of available tags that then filters
  the books available. These tags can include \"lendable\" (the book
  is currently free to borrow), \"public\" (the book is in the public
  domain), or \"print-restricted\" (saving the book in print form is
  disabled by the publisher). Further tags may be made available in
  this fashion.

- **Improve mobile experience** --- The user
  experience on all mobile devices can be of the same level of quality
  as traditional desktop users. By leveraging responsive design and
  integrating CSS media queries into the existing front-end codebase,
  the Open Library can provide for any user regardless of what device
  they may have.

- **Create authoritative book pages** ---
  Different editions of a given book should not be presented as
  different book entitities themselves. Instead, there should exist an
  official page for a given book, where various editions can be
  stored. In this way, users are not presented with a list of
  different books should multiple editions exist.

